# GameManagers Guide

## Manager Responsibilities (one-line each)
- **GridManager** ‚Äî Central hub. Isometric 2D grid, cell access, coordinate conversion, building placement, bulldozing, sorting order, pathfinding
- **TerrainManager** ‚Äî Heightmap generation, slope types, prefab selection by slope
- **WaterManager** ‚Äî Water body generation and management (multi-level lakes: **FEAT-37**; **FEAT-37a** / **FEAT-37b** / **FEAT-37c** completed; shore **BUG-33**; load building sort **BUG-34** completed; multi-cell footprint **BUG-35**; `.cursor/specs/water-system-refactor.md`)
- **ForestManager** ‚Äî Forest generation (sparse/medium/dense), forestation, deforestation
- **ZoneManager** ‚Äî RCI zoning (residential, commercial, industrial), zone tile placement
- **RoadManager** ‚Äî Road drawing, prefab selection by neighbors, road preview
- **InterstateManager** ‚Äî Interstate highways connecting the map to the exterior
- **GeographyManager** ‚Äî Orchestrator for all terrain initialization (terrain + water + forest + grid)
- **DemandManager** ‚Äî R/C/I demand calculation based on population, employment, forests
- **EconomyManager** ‚Äî Taxes, money, financial transactions
- **CityStats** ‚Äî Global statistics aggregator: population, employment, water/power capacity
- **EmploymentManager** ‚Äî Employment and unemployment calculation by zone
- **SimulationManager** ‚Äî Automatic simulation cycle orchestrator
- **AutoRoadBuilder** ‚Äî Automatic road network extension
- **AutoZoningManager** ‚Äî Automatic zoning of cells adjacent to roads
- **AutoResourcePlanner** ‚Äî Automatic resource building planning
- **GrowthManager** ‚Äî Zone growth logic
- **GrowthBudgetManager** ‚Äî Growth budget per category
- **UrbanizationProposalManager** ‚Äî Urban expansion proposals
- **UIManager** ‚Äî Main UI: popups, toolbar/tool state (`ControlPanel` in `MainScene.unity`), demand bar; UI program: `docs/ui-design-system-project.md`, context `docs/ui-design-system-context.md`, spec `.cursor/specs/ui-design-system.md` (toolbar **¬ß3.3**; layout migration **TECH-07**)
- **CursorManager** ‚Äî Placement preview, visual cursor
- **TimeManager** ‚Äî Game speed control, simulation ticks
- **GameNotificationManager** ‚Äî Singleton. In-game notifications
- **GameSaveManager** ‚Äî Serialize/deserialize game state
- **GameManager** ‚Äî Entry point, game loading
- **RegionalMapManager** ‚Äî Regional map with neighboring cities
- **StatisticsManager** ‚Äî Historical trend tracking
- **AnimatorManager** (AnimationManager.cs) ‚Äî Animation control
- **GameDebugInfoBuilder** ‚Äî Debug text generation for game state

## Helper Services (extracted from managers)
- **GridPathfinder** ‚Äî A* pathfinding for road routes
- **GridSortingOrderService** ‚Äî Sorting order computation
- **BuildingPlacementService** ‚Äî Building placement and load/restore
- **TerraformingService** ‚Äî Path-level terraform plan computation
- **PathTerraformPlan** ‚Äî Terraform Apply/Revert, cut-through mode
- **RoadPrefabResolver** ‚Äî Prefab selection for path and single-cell contexts
- **RoadPathCostConstants** ‚Äî Shared cost constants for road pathfinding
- **UrbanCentroidService** ‚Äî Urban centroid and ring calculation (FEAT-32)
- **GameBootstrap** ‚Äî Entry point, game loading flow

## Rules
- **Road terraform validation:** Use `RoadManager.TryPrepareRoadPlacementPlan` (includes `PathTerraformPlan.TryValidatePhase1Heights`) and `RoadPathValidationContext`. Streets / auto-road should use `TryPrepareRoadPlacementPlanLongestValidPrefix` when partial paths are acceptable; interstate uses full-path `TryPrepareRoadPlacementPlan` with `forbidCutThrough: true`. Do not use `ComputePathPlan` alone for placement decisions. Specs: `.cursor/specs/road-drawing-fixes.md` (BUG-25), `.cursor/specs/interstate-prefab-and-pathfinding-fixes.md` (BUG-27/BUG-29 completed per BACKLOG).
- Every manager is a MonoBehaviour living as a component on a scene GameObject
- NEVER instantiate managers with `new` ‚Äî they are always scene components
- GridManager is the central hub ‚Äî all cell operations go through it
- For notifications use `GameNotificationManager.Instance`
- CityStats is the global data aggregator ‚Äî read city-wide stats from here
